  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The only-- either a minor or because I was away from home and they probably couldn't find me, or whatever the situation may have been.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And at that time, I was only 14 years old-- 14 and 1/2, maybe 15.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And of course, it was very-- I-- there was very little I could do.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I didn't have the know-how to go back to this village and collect all that stuff.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was very difficult.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I managed a little bit, but it was very, very difficult for me.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "On the 8th of November of 1938, we heard that a vice ambassador, or whatever his rank was, of the German-- in the German embassy in Paris got assassinated by a Jew by the name of Herschel Grynszpan, who in fact was the son of that Grynszpan family that incidentally, later on, I met when I got to Poland, who were so upset, who most likely got similar message as I did, that his parents got kicked out from Germany and are without a home, and whatever, and experiencing tremendous hardship.",
      "word_count": 91
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So he bought himself a gun.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He wanted to see the ambassador-- could get only as far as the vice ambassador by the name of vom Rath, and killed him.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I believe that was on the 8th of November of 1938.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there was a lot of write-ups, all over the world, in-- in publications everywhere, about the incident.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "On November 11th, two days later, my boss, the engineer Guggenheim-- we were working there install-- installing some electrical [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] systems, in a Jewish factory incidentally-- still, at that time.",
      "word_count": 33
    }
  ],
